62. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A9AB999238551E8D1FE46D66BF1BA" authority="(Walker, 1849) (Dolichopodinae)" authorityName="Dolichopodinae" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[193,826,440,468]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chetifer">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D1FE46D73EF1BD" bold="true" box="[193,623,440,467]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D1FE46D4EBF1BD" bold="true" box="[193,442,440,467]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Hercostomus chetifer</emphasis>
(Walker, 1849)
</emphasis>
(Dolichopodinae)
</taxonomicName>
— 
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551EB48FE46D144F1BD" bold="true" box="[856,1045,441,467]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
new to 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EBBDFE46D144F1BD" box="[941,1045,441,467]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350B2B199238551E887FDFED7D0F29D" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E887FDFED77FF275" blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[151,558,512,539]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E887FDFED743F275" bold="true" box="[151,530,512,539]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FDDBD066F251" blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,1335,548,575]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FDDBD430F251" bold="true" box="[199,353,548,575]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EA87FDDAD7ABF251" box="[663,762,549,575]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three northern provinces and Algarve in the south.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FDB6D19DF2C5" blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FDB6D47DF20D" bold="true" box="[199,300,585,611]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
Most of the capture locations of this species in 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551EB5EFDB6D6FCF20D" box="[846,941,585,611]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
were situated along open water (waterfalls, marshlands, riverbanks). In northwestern Europe, the species is generally considered as part of the hygropetric fauna (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB9CCB99238551E8F4FD6ED43AF2C5" author="Pollet, M." box="[228,363,657,683]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F35DA1AA99238551E98CFD6ED4BFF2C5" box="[412,494,657,683]" name="Croatia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Croatia</collectingCountry>
it is found to prefer riverbeds to springs (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB9CCB99238551EBD0FD6ED191F2C5" author="Pollet, M. &amp; Ivkovic, M." box="[960,1216,657,683]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="401 - 428" refId="ref35148" refString="Pollet, M. &amp; Ivkovic, M. (2018) Dolichopodidae of riverbeds and springs in Croatia with an updated checklist of Croatia (Diptera). Zootaxa, 4455 (3), 401 - 428. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4455.3.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Pollet &amp; Ivković 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FD4BD499F2A1" blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,456,692,719]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FD4BD400F2A1" bold="true" box="[199,337,692,719]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
4.6 (rare).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF5E13A99238551E8D7FD27D7D0F29D" blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,641,728,755]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B93E3D2899238551E8D7FD27D4D3F29D" bold="true" box="[199,386,728,755]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
May, July, September.
</paragraph>
